title: Electron v0.35
body:
I updated type definitions for Electron v0.35 because @jedmao currently doesn't have any plan to fix it (answered in #7046).
## API changes for Electron v0.35

Electron v0.35 has some breaking changes in APIs.
1. `electron` module was defined and all previous modules were put in it.
2. Many options for `BrowserWindowOptions` are renamed because of change of naming style (e.g. `max-height` -> `maxHeight`
3. Renamed `Url` to `URL`

Only 3. was already reflected to previous `github-electron.d.ts`.

So I updated 1. and 2.
## Unite type definitions for renderer process and main process

I did this because `github-electron-main.d.ts` and `github-electron-renderer.d.ts` can't be used at the same time because `tsd.d.ts` includes both definition files and they collided each other.
So I decided to unite them to one `github-electron.d.ts` file.

I left `github-electron-renderer-tests.ts` and `github-electron-main-tests.ts` separated because actual codes for Electron app are separated like that.
## Defined interface for `webPreferences` options

I added this because `webPreferences` property of `BrowserWindowOptions` were defined as `any`.  And I moved some options from `BrowserWindowOptions` to `WebPreferences` because they had been moved in the past.

title: jsSHA browser global definition & test.
body:
Pull request #6891 removed the global `jsSHA` definition. The test would have caught this error, but that pull request also removed the test. This global var definitely exists, is used by people in production, and [can be seen in the jsSHA source here](https://github.com/Caligatio/jsSHA/blob/de0cf6817e2125388c39ffc2a478ff4f8a69405a/src/sha_dev.js#L1698).

I have added back both the definition and the test for it.
